  ],
  "rationale": "The EBO postprocessor returns higher scores for ID samples (confidence). The official OpenOOD metrics.py negates scores before roc_auc_score because it treats OOD as positive. Our compute_auroc function already treats ID as positive (labels=1 for ID, 0 for OOD), so we must NOT negate scores. The negation caused the ~12% AUROC (inverted from ~88%). Removing the negation restores correct polarity."
}
